<%- include('partials/header') %>

<section class="relative w-full min-h-[60vh] sm:min-h-[65vh] lg:h-[75vh] flex items-end pb-12 sm:pb-16 px-4 sm:px-8 lg:px-24 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 z-0">
        <img src="/images/Career_Header.jpg" alt="Medical Professionals and Engineers" class="w-full h-full object-cover">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-t from-iitkNavy via-iitkNavy/50 to-transparent"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="relative z-10 w-full max-w-4xl p-6 sm:p-10 lg:p-12 glass-panel">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-iitkbluelight mb-4">
            <a href="/" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Home</a>
            <div class="w-4 h-[1px] bg-white/40"></div>
            <span class="text-white">Careers</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="font-heading text-3xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-black text-white mb-4 tracking-tight">Careers at FMRT</h1>
        <p class="text-sm sm:text-lg text-gray-100 font-light leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
            Join a team that is reshaping the future of healthcare in India. We seek passionate professionals at the intersection of medicine, technology, and social impact.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="py-16 sm:py-24 px-4 sm:px-8 lg:px-24 max-w-7xl mx-auto">
    <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-12 lg:gap-16 items-start">
        
        <div class="w-full lg:w-1/3 lg:sticky lg:top-32 space-y-8">
            <div class="bg-white p-6 sm:p-8 rounded-xl border-t-4 border-iitkNavy shadow-sm">
                <span class="text-iitkTeal font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-xs mb-2 block">Why Work With Us</span>
                <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-iitkNavy mb-4">Be Part of Something Historic</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed space-y-4">
                    FMRT-IIT Kanpur is building India's first truly interdisciplinary medical innovation ecosystem. This is a once-in-a-generation opportunity to work at the frontier of healthcare, research, and technology — backed by the prestige of IIT Kanpur and the support of India's most generous philanthropists.
                </p>
                <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-xs sm:text-sm text-gray-600 border-t pt-4">
                    <li><strong class="text-iitkNavy">🏆 Institutional Excellence:</strong> Work within the ecosystem of IIT Kanpur — one of India's premier research institutions with a 60+ year legacy of engineering excellence.</li>
                    <li><strong class="text-iitkNavy">🔬 Innovation-First Environment:</strong> Collaborate with researchers, clinicians, engineers, and entrepreneurs to solve real healthcare problems at scale.</li>
                    <li><strong class="text-iitkNavy">🌍 National Social Impact:</strong> Your work will directly affect the health and wellbeing of millions of people in Eastern UP and across India.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-hospitalLight p-6 sm:p-8 rounded-xl border border-gray-200">
                <h4 class="font-heading font-bold text-iitkNavy text-lg mb-3">How to Apply</h4>
                <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-xs sm:text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                    <li>Review the open positions listed below.</li>
                    <li>Prepare your updated CV and a cover letter addressed to the HR team.</li>
                    <li>Click the Apply button or email your application to <a href="mailto:hr1_fmrt@iitk.ac.in" class="text-iitkTeal font-bold hover:underline">hr1_fmrt@iitk.ac.in</a>.</li>
                    <li>Shortlisted candidates will be contacted for interviews within 7 working days.</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="w-full lg:w-2/3 space-y-6">
            <span class="text-iitkTeal font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-xs mb-2 block">Open Positions</span>
            <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-extrabold text-iitkNavy mb-6">Current Job Openings</h2>

            <div class="bg-white p-6 sm:p-8 lg:p-10 rounded-xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm flex flex-col hover:border-iitkTeal/30 transition-colors">
                <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-xl sm:text-2xl text-iitkNavy mb-3">Chief Human Resources Officer (CHRO)</h3>
                <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
                    <span class="bg-hospitalLight text-iitkNavy text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-widest px-2.5 py-1 rounded">📍 Kanpur, UP</span>
                    <span class="bg-hospitalLight text-iitkNavy text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-widest px-2.5 py-1 rounded">Senior Leadership</span>
                    <span class="bg-hospitalLight text-iitkNavy text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-widest px-2.5 py-1 rounded">Full-Time</span>
                </div>
                <p class="text-[10px] font-bold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">Posted: 29 May 2026</p>
                <p class="text-gray-600 text-xs sm:text-sm leading-relaxed mb-6">
                    <strong>Description:</strong> The CHRO / HR Head will be responsible for leading and establishing the overall Human Resources function for the organization. The role involves driving HR strategy, workforce planning, talent acquisition, employee engagement, organizational development, policy formulation, and culture-building initiatives to support the growth and operational excellence of the hospital.
                </p>
                <h4 class="font-bold text-iitkNavy text-sm mb-2">Key Responsibilities:</h4>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-xs text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                    <li>Develop and lead the overall HR strategy aligned with the organization’s vision.</li>
                    <li>Establish HR policies, processes, systems, and organizational structures.</li>
                    <li>Lead talent acquisition and workforce planning for clinical, non-clinical, and admin functions.</li>
                    <li>Drive employee engagement, performance management, and retention initiatives.</li>
                    <li>Ensure compliance with labour laws, statutory requirements, and HR governance standards.</li>
                    <li>Collaborate with leadership teams on organizational planning, manpower budgeting, and strategic decision-making.</li>
                    <li>Handle employee relations, grievance management, disciplinary matters, and conflict resolution.</li>
                    <li>Build a strong organizational culture focused on professionalism, collaboration, and growth.</li>
                    <li>Lead HR analytics, MIS reporting, and workforce performance monitoring.</li>
                    <li>Manage and mentor the HR team while ensuring smooth coordination across departments.</li>
                </ul>
                <div class="pt-4 border-t border-gray-100 mt-auto flex">
                    <a href="mailto:hr1_fmrt@iitk.ac.in?subject=Application for CHRO" class="btn-primary px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-bold text-xs uppercase tracking-wider">Apply For This Position →</a>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white p-6 sm:p-8 lg:p-10 rounded-xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm flex flex-col hover:border-iitkTeal/30 transition-colors">
                <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-xl sm:text-2xl text-iitkNavy mb-3">Chief Financial Officer (CFO)</h3>
                <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
                    <span class="bg-hospitalLight text-iitkNavy text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-widest px-2.5 py-1 rounded">📍 Kanpur, UP</span>
                    <span class="bg-hospitalLight text-iitkNavy text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-widest px-2.5 py-1 rounded">Senior Leadership</span>
                    <span class="bg-hospitalLight text-iitkNavy text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-widest px-2.5 py-1 rounded">Full-Time</span>
                </div>
                <p class="text-[10px] font-bold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">Posted: 30 May 2026</p>
                <p class="text-gray-600 text-xs sm:text-sm leading-relaxed mb-6">
                    <strong>Description:</strong> The Head Finance / CFO will oversee the overall financial operations of the company, ensuring financial stability, regulatory compliance, budgeting, revenue management, and strategic financial planning. The role involves supporting organizational growth through effective financial control, reporting, and operational efficiency.
                </p>
                <h4 class="font-bold text-iitkNavy text-sm mb-2">Key Responsibilities:</h4>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-xs text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                    <li>Lead financial planning, budgeting, and forecasting for the hospital.</li>
                    <li>Monitor hospital revenue, billing, collections, cash flow, and financial performance.</li>
                    <li>Ensure timely preparation of financial statements, MIS reports, and dashboards.</li>
                    <li>Maintain compliance with statutory, taxation, audit, and regulatory requirements.</li>
                    <li>Manage banking operations, treasury functions, and cash flow management.</li>
                    <li>Work closely with operations and procurement teams for cost optimization and financial efficiency</li>
                    <li>Support management in strategic decision-making, expansion planning, and business growth initiatives</li>
                    <li>Lead and manage the finance and accounts team while ensuring smooth interdepartmental coordination</li>
                    <li>Coordinate with external stakeholders including auditors, taxation authorities, MCA, Credit rating agencies, statutory bodies, and other vendor authorities</li>
                    <li>Present audit committee findings and financial reports to the Company Board</li>
                </ul>
                <div class="pt-4 border-t border-gray-100 mt-auto flex">
                    <a href="mailto:hr1_fmrt@iitk.ac.in?subject=Application for CFO" class="btn-primary px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-bold text-xs uppercase tracking-wider">Apply For This Position →</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="bg-white p-6 sm:p-8 lg:p-10 rounded-xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm flex flex-col hover:border-iitkTeal/30 transition-colors">
                <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-xl sm:text-2xl text-iitkNavy mb-3">Learning & Development (L&D) Head</h3>
                <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
                    <span class="bg-hospitalLight text-iitkNavy text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-widest px-2.5 py-1 rounded">📍 Kanpur, UP</span>
                    <span class="bg-hospitalLight text-iitkNavy text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-widest px-2.5 py-1 rounded">Senior Leadership</span>
                    <span class="bg-hospitalLight text-iitkNavy text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-widest px-2.5 py-1 rounded">Full-Time</span>
                </div>
                <p class="text-[10px] font-bold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">Posted: 30 May 2026</p>
                <p class="text-gray-600 text-xs sm:text-sm leading-relaxed mb-6">
                    <strong>Description:</strong> The Learning & Development (L&D) Head will be responsible for establishing and leading the training, learning, and capability development function for the hospital. The role involves creating structured learning systems, enhancing employee competencies, supporting clinical and non-clinical workforce development.
                </p>
                <h4 class="font-bold text-iitkNavy text-sm mb-2">Key Responsibilities:</h4>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-xs text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                <li>Develop and implement the overall Learning & Development strategy for the hospital.</li>
                    <li>Identify training and development needs across clinical, nursing, allied health, administrative, and support functions.</li>
                    <li>Design and execute induction, onboarding, orientation, and employee development programs.</li>
                    <li>Develop competency-based training frameworks and learning pathways for employees.</li>
                    <li>Coordinate technical, behavioral, leadership, compliance, and soft-skill training programs.</li>
                    <li>Collaborate with department heads and leadership teams to align learning initiatives with organizational objectives.</li>
                    <li>Establish succession planning and leadership development initiatives.</li>
                    <li>Monitor training effectiveness through assessments, feedback, audits, and performance outcomes.</li>
                    <li>Maintain training calendars, learning records, compliance documentation, and development dashboards.</li>
                    <li>Coordinate with external trainers, faculty, consultants, and academic/training partners.</li>
                    <li>Support employee engagement, culture-building, and organizational development initiatives.</li>
                    <li>Lead and manage the L&D function while ensuring effective coordination across departments.</li>
                </ul>
                <div class="pt-4 border-t border-gray-100 mt-auto flex">
                    <a href="mailto:hr1_fmrt@iitk.ac.in?subject=Application for L&D Head" class="btn-primary px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-bold text-xs uppercase tracking-wider">Apply For This Position →</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>